main event: A round, white object approximately 10,000 feet in altitude was observed traveling at high speed over Gillespie Field in San Diego, California on June 6, 1955.
interesting points: The object was round in shape and white in color.
It traveled at a high rate of speed in a straight line.
The sighting was observed by multiple military personnel, including a Lieutenant Colonel, two Lieutenants, and two Technical Sergeants.
Additional information indicates that a NOTI-19 balloon was launched from Lowry and plotted over San Diego just minutes after the sighting, suggesting the object may have been a balloon.
witnesses: Lt. Col. USAF (pilot), Lt. USAF, Ft. Sggn. USAF, Ft. Sggn. USAF
